des: KOKO LP, low-power radio station broadcasts at 96.3FM in Hana town out of the historic Courthouse building at the Hana Cultural Center, and streams worldwide, playing commercial-free Hawaiian music and local cultural and community programming. We feature a broad playlist of vintage, classic and modern Hawaiian music across diverse genres, including many obscure tracks that you’re unlikely to hear anywhere else! KOKO Radio's Mission: To provide a voice for Native Hawaiians. To nurture, perpetuate, and celebrate Hawaiian values through the medium of radio using Hawaiian music, Hawaiian language, and Hawaiian cultural programming.
